+ * Translates musl's (addr, FUTEX_WAIT, val, struct timespec * relative)
+ * shape into Thylacine's (addr, expected, timeout_us) shape. The relative
+ * timespec already comes from __timedwait_cp's absolute-to-relative
+ * conversion (clock_gettime + subtract); torpor's relative microsecond
+ * timeout is the direct match. timeout = NULL is "block indefinitely"
+ * (timeout_us = -1).
